.TH "tar" "1" "" "seed 0.1.0"
.SH NAME
tar \- create, extract, and list tar archives
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tar \-c[fjJzOvk] ARCHIVE [FILE...]
.B tar \-x[fjJzOvkO] ARCHIVE [MEMBER...]
.B tar \-t[fjJzv] ARCHIVE [MEMBER...]
.B tar \-\-help
.SH DESCRIPTION
tar supports create, extract, and list modes with traditional short options, including old\-style forms such as 'tar xf archive.tar'.
.PP
Extraction supports GNU\-compatible \-\-strip\-components and \-\-overwrite behavior for common packaging and build\-script workflows.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-c
Create an archive.
.TP
.B \-x
Extract an archive.
.TP
.B \-t
List archive contents.
.TP
.B \-f FILE
Use FILE as the archive path. Use '\-' for standard input or output.
.TP
.B \-C DIR
Change to DIR before processing following file operands.
.TP
.B \-v
Print member names as they are processed.
.TP
.B \-O
Write extracted file contents to standard output.
.TP
.B \-k
Keep existing files when extracting.
.TP
.B \-z, \-j, \-J
Use gzip, bzip2, or xz compression.
.TP
.B \-X FILE
Read exclude patterns from FILE.
.TP
.B \-\-overwrite
Overwrite existing files during extraction.
.TP
.B \-\-strip\-components N
Strip N leading path components when extracting.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show a short usage summary.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B tar czf archive.tar.gz dir
Create a gzip\-compressed archive from dir.
.TP
.B tar xf archive.tar \-\-strip\-components=1
Extract an archive while dropping the first path component from each member.
.SH SEE ALSO
gzip(1), bzip2(1), xz(1)
